<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8" /><title>simple form styled</title><style type="text/css">/**** LAYOUT ****/#wrapper {width: 960px;margin: 0 auto;}#sidebar {width: 450px;float: left;}#content {margin-left: 470px;}.comment {padding: 10px;border: 1px dotted silver;border-bottom: none;}.comment:last-child {border-bottom: 1px dotted silver;}article.comment:nth-child(odd) {background-color: #f8f8f8;}article.comment:nth-child(even) {background-color: #efefef;}.comment footer {font-size: .8em;}.comment p {margin: 0;margin-bottom: 2px;}/**** FORM ****/form {	border: 1px dotted silver;	padding: 4px;	background-color: #f8f8f8;	margin: 0 auto;	}fieldset {	padding: 10px;	margin-bottom: 20px;	text-transform: uppercase;	background-color: #efefef;	border: 1px dotted silver;	}label {font-style: italic;}label.text-input {	display: block;	float: left;	width: 150px;	text-transform: capitalize;	}	input.submit {	margin-left: 20px;	}h1 {text-align: center;}</style></head><body><div id="wrapper"><header><h1>Amazing Comment Page!</h1></header><aside id="sidebar"><form id="example" name="example" method="post" action="display-comment-script.php"><input type="hidden" name="phpday" value="<?php echo date('l'); ?>" /><fieldset><legend>Submit a Comment</legend><label class="text-input" for="firstname">First Name</label><input type="text" name="firstname" id="firstname" /><br /><label class="text-input" for="lastname">Last Name</label><input type="text" name="lastname" id="lastname" /><br /><label  class="text-input" for="comments">Your Comments:</label><textarea name="comments" id="comments" rows="10" cols="30"></textarea></fieldset><input type="submit" name="submitbutton" id="submitbutton" value="Submit" class="submit" /></form></aside><article id="content"><h2>Your Comments</h2><?php//This is the script that will retrieve the comments from the database and display them when the page loads. When you submit a new comment, the page will reload with the new comment included! Slick!//write the variables for your connection and your query. Remember that you'll get a result resource that is array-like, and the while loop will allow you to use the result resource (with its keys - the keys match the names of the columns) however you like.$connect = mysqli_connect('localhost', 'Jessica', 'J1u2n3e4', 'php_class')	or die('error connecting to database');$query = "SELECT * FROM comments";$result = mysqli_query($connect, $query)	or die ('error querying database');// now write the while loop that will take the result resource and do something with it. The something we want is for the comments to get printed to the page. Remember that each comment could be considered a stand-alone article in HTML5; we're thinking like WordPress even though our comment information is pretty flimsy. :-)?>		<?php	while ($row = mysqli_fetch_array($result)) { ?><article class="comment">	<p>		<?php	echo $row['comments']; ?>	</p>	<footer>		<?php echo $row['first_name'].' '.$row['last_name'] ?> on <?php echo $row['phpday'] ?>.	</footer></article></php	} ?><!--  you want each comment to be in its own article, and that article needs the class of "comment" (<article class="comment">). The comment is in a paragraph tag. The footer holds the name of the poster and the day the post was made. After the commenter and the day are printed to the footer, close the footer and close the article. use the powerpoint as an example of how to "break up" the html and the scripts in the while loop.  if your content prints properly, the styles above will style it! You won't need to do anything! -->?>	</article></div></body></html>